classes.name: Heated Vinyasa Flow - IN STUDIO HOHOKUS
classes.activities: Cycling, Dance, Rowing, Boxing, Running, Pilates, Strength Training, Outdoors, Sports, Free, Barre, Martial Arts, Bootcamp
classes.description:
This class class was designed with the intention of offering a middle-ground between their super sweaty, heated vinyasa and their non-heated flow class by setting temperature to a comfortably warm 75-80 degrees. You can expect all of the same elements that you receive in their other signature flow classes - an inventive and vigorous flowing of postures guided by deep and steady breath, along with the added ingredient of a glistening, purifying sweat. This delicious and energizing practice will of course end with a blissful savansana to soak in all the benefits of the practice.

This is the perfect class for those looking to transition their practice into a warmer environment, or those who are just looking to achieve enhanced sweat.

venues.name: Fit4Dance
venues.description: Fit4Dance is dedicated to bringing quality and affordable dance and fitness instruction to women and children in Brooklyn. They offer a comfortable space where women can have fun, learn to dance, improve their fitness and health, meet new people, explore other cultures, and freely express themselves. Laci established Fit4Dance to inspire and motivate women to take control of their health and have a blast doing it! Not only does she want to inspire and motivate women about health and fitness through dance; she intends to provide a fun, inspirational dance space for youth as well. They offer the following dance and fitness classes: Afrobeats, Afrocuban, Ballet, Bellydance Hall, Bootcamp, Haitian Dance, Jazz, Modern, Sensual Stretch, & Soca.

classes.name: SKY TING Yoga
classes.activities: Cycling, Dance, Rowing, Boxing, Running, Pilates, Strength Training, Outdoors, Sports, Free, Barre, Hair, Food and Drink, Yoga, Nails, Martial Arts, Bootcamp
classes.description: The yoga we teach is a medley of lineages. All styles of yoga have something important to offer and we steal from them all! Cross-pollinating yogic material allows us to create something wholly new yet refined with rich substance and history. In biology, monocultures are highly susceptible to disease and death. Likewise, we believe that braiding a diverse pool of influences helps us create the strongest possible offering for the physical, emotional and cultural health and well being of our wonderful community. The primary traditions we study and borrow from most are Katonah, Taoist, Hatha and Vinyasa, as well as several different meditation and breathing practices.Classes are open to all levels of experience from beginner to advanced.

classes.name: Hot Power Hour
classes.description: Hot Powerflow Vinyasa is our signature, upbeat yoga practice that gets you out of your head and back into your body. Youll work hard to link together your movements and breath while you flow through a series of traditional yoga poses. Its a sweaty, powerful and meditative experience that will help you turn down the noise of everyday life. This open-level class is set to music. Modifications and variations will be offered to tailor the practice to your individual needs.IN-STUDIO POLICY:As we gradually open to full capacity we will still have capacity limitations. We encourage you to continue to pre-register for classes. If you decide to walk in please know there is a chance the class is full and you will not be able to take class.If you are unable to attend, cancel your reservation 8 hours prior to the start time. If you do not attend class and have not canceled, you will lose the class from your package (single drop-ins or numbered packages) or be charged $25 if you have an Unlimited Package (applies to: Intro Offers, Unlimited Month, Power Plus Membership or 1 Year Unlimited). For Class Pass cancellations, requests must be made through Class Pass. Class Pass is not accepted at all locations.Rental Mats and straps are not available at this time. Communal Blocks are available for use. Please clean blocks after use. We ask that you limit items brought into the studio. Only bring your own mat, blocks, straps, and towels. Cell phones are not permitted in the hot room.Showers and dressing rooms are open.Class will be set to 98 degrees with 40% humidity.

venues.name: Liftonic
venues.description: LIFTONIC is a group weight training studio that focuses on building and toning muscle for a strong, lean physique. Classes consist of a 50min sequence performed on and around a weights bench using dumbbells incorporating traditional weights exercises together with abdominal/core and full body movements. They believe in developing mental and physical strength through medium to low repetition sets which makes LIFTONIC the perfect accompaniment for your current HIIT/Yoga/Pilates fitness regime. Classes are suitable to all fitness and strength levels as you select the weight for each exercise that works for you.

classes.name: Legs, Butt & Back (Studio) (LT BURN)
classes.description: Amazing things happen when you target large muscle groups with true weight training exercises. Our signature class format focuses on Squats, Lunges, Rows and more. Get inspired to lift heavy and watch your body transform! Low to medium repetition sets of leg and back exercises combined is a killer combination. Add in some isolated butt exercises including exercise bands and you have a non-stop weight training class that delivers results
